{{Infobox anthem |title = {{lang|ar|نشيد وطني موريتاني}} |english_title = National Anthem of Mauritania |image = |image_size = |en_alt_title = "National Anthem of the Islamic Republic of Mauritania" |prefix = National |country = {{MRT}} |author = Baba Ould Cheikh |lyrics_date = late 18th century |composer = [[Tolia Nikiprowetzky]] |music_date = 1960 |adopted = 1960 |until = 16 November 2017 |sound = Former national anthem of Mauritania (1960–2017), performed by the U.S. Navy Band.oga |sound_title = "Former national Anthem of the Islamic Republic of Mauritania" (instrumental) }}
The "'''National Anthem of the Islamic Republic of Mauritania'''" was [[Mauritania]]'s former [[national anthem]] between 1960 and 2017. Its lyrics are taken from a poem written in the late 18th century by Baba Ould Cheikh. The melody was arranged by [[Tolia Nikiprowetzky]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://nationalanthems.me/mauritania-national-anthem-of-mauritania/ | title=National Anthem of Mauritania | publisher=NationalAnthems.me | accessdate=2012-02-24 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nationalanthems.info/mr-17.htm | title=Mauritania (1960–2017) | publisher=NationalAnthems.me | accessdate=2018-08-03 }}</ref> The anthem was adopted upon independence [[French Mauritania|from France]] in 1960. The unusual and highly complex rhythm of it makes it extremely difficult to sing; for this reason it is often erroneously listed as wordless.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nationalanthems.info/mr-17.htm | title=Mauritania (1960–2017) | publisher=NationalAnthems.me | accessdate=2018-03-17 }}</ref> The anthem was replaced by the [[National anthem of Mauritania|current national anthem]] on 16 November 2017, after the [[Mauritanian constitutional referendum, 2017|Mauritanian constitutional referendum of 2017]].
