'''Whitey''' is a slang term for a white person, mostly of non-[[Mediterranean race|Mediterranean]] European ancestry, often used in a pejorative manner.<ref name=OED>{{cite web|title=Whitey|url=http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/us/definition/american_english/whitey|website=oxforddictionaries.com|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref> Whitey is used in juxtaposition to other ethnic slurs based upon a race's skin color, such as [[Redskin (slang)|redskin]] and [[negro]]. The level of contempt held with the term varies, but one of the more severe pejorative examples is shown by the "Kill Whitey" tattoo on the cheek of [[Maruse Heath]].<ref name=nyp_kill_whitey>{{cite news|last1=Italiano|first1=Laura|title=‘Kill Whitey’ Panther is held on gun rap|url=https://nypost.com/2013/06/22/kill-whitey-panther-is-held-on-gun-rap/|accessdate=26 September 2014|publisher=New York Post|date=June 22, 2013|ref=‘Kill Whitey’ Panther is held on gun rap}}</ref>
It is difficult to trace the origin,{{according to whom|date=September 2014}} but presumably it is derived from "white" as [[color terminology for race]]. There are many examples of the term being used in pop culture from [[Michelle Obama]] denying that she used the term and instead said "that’s something that [[George Jefferson]] would say."<ref>{{cite news | author=Michael Powell and Jodi Kantor | title=Michelle Obama Looks for a New Introduction | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/18/us/politics/18michelle.html | publisher=New York Times | date=2008-06-18 | accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref> [[Richard Pryor]] also used the term on national television on a [[Saturday Night Live]] skit in 1975.<ref name=pryorwhitey>{{cite web| title=IMDB.com, Quotes, Saturday Night Live, Richard Pryor |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0694453/quotes|website=www.imdb.com|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref>
